The song is about "alcoholism and depression", look at the apartment, the disorder and the things on the floor, it seems like the home of a depressed person, the dancer is totally alone, nobody accompanies her in her suffering.
The phrase "push it down" refers to whether or not to drink a glass.
The phrase "Help me" is a call for help, but it goes almost unnoticed.
The dance also has many meanings, she dances playing someone drunk and depressed, she shows all her emotions without anyone caring, no one is watching her.
The dancer (Maddie Ziegler) has her hands painted pink, this means blood from suicide attempts, the author did not want to use red to avoid being so controversial.
There is a lot of meaning in the dance, almost everything has to do with the context of the song, the rest is dance to accompany and make transitions.

At 00:12 I am a party girl, I am with a drink in my hand, do I drink it or not drink it? I push it down and I raise it again, I am undecided, I have to leave it, when will I learn?
At 00:27 she talks on the phone and is invited to go out partying, while holding a glass of wine. It is time to drink nonstop and lose your mind.
At 00:55 I am hurt, I am like a dog in a wheelchair that crawls with wheels towards the corner, but I get up with difficulty.
At 01:00 Everything has passed, now I am happy for life and without worries, everything is fine. But then I fall back from above, time to drink and do crazy things, to have a good time.
At 01:22 the stomach demands food. I'm drunk, I almost lose my balance. I say goodbye with a kiss to everyone. Nobody helps me, don't worry about me, I hold my hair myself and go.
At 01:34 it is time to sit down to eat spaghetti, I take the fork I stab it on the wall and throw it. Now I have passed out and I wake up again, I scare the flies on each side, now a cockroach climbs the wall, I clean my mouth, the food was horrible, now my stomach hurts.
At 02:01 Playing dice, I am now a gansgter. I shake and shake the bad off me, I go to a corner to cry.
At 02:24 she runs to the window but stops and turns with a scared face and backs up with trembling steps.
At 02:32 she cuts her veins in each hand and says goodbye, then she goes to the street and knocks on doors for help, nobody responds.
At 02:42 she leans against the wall, she is exhausted and depressed, she is about to fall apart. Pause the minute 02:44, it is the best scene, you can see his depressed face and his body about to fall. Then she runs jumping every obstacle on her way.
At 02:56 I open my eye, I hardly have any signs of life. The tears run down her face, she tries to commit suicide by hanging herself with the curtains, her air runs out and she says goodbye to everyone (she observes that the curtains have blood stains).
At 03:12 I am looking for someone to take refuge in, but love is not pious with me, I repress it, I repress it.
At 03:26 It is time to get up and continue pretending before everyone, I walk a tightrope and smile falsely at everyone, my face changes from happy to sad, I lie to them, I'm fine.
"Chandelier" is about someone drunk, imagine someone who drinks until they lose their minds and don't care about anything, hangs on even a candlestick, let's live regardless of tomorrow.
The video has many more meanings than the ones I have mentioned and is fully choreographed.

For anyone who wants to know the storyline between the videos listen here!

So the whole thing starts with The Hills in which The Weeknd gets in a car crash and then he emerges as well as a girl with him. The car in this video is actually a representation of his old self (Trilogy Weeknd) and when he emerges from the now destroyed car it is his new mainstream self (the freeform dreads represent this and he is very aware of the mainstream route hes taking btw), the girl is the fans always nagging at him to go back to who he used to be and keep nagging at him until the car explodes representing theres no more "old" Weeknd anymore this is who he is now. So he keeps walking until he walks into a mansion where in the top room there is genderless person (I really dont what gender it is), with a bunch of sexualized girls around it (also note the room is tinted red like hell), this person represents the devil.

The story line continues in I Cant Feel My Face where Mr. XO is performing on a stage at a classy bar it seems. This video doesnt really have much until we see the devil (the genderless person) looking deeply at the Weeknd. This implys that the devil is the music industry making him perform, as when he sees this person his dancing intensifies until the devil catches him on fire. This shows he will perform through anything just to get the person (devil/music industry) to like him, this makes sense considering his last album was great but definetly more mainstream than previously before.

Then we go to Tell Your Friends where at the very beginning the new mainstream Weeknd is burying the old one, but you can see the old Weeknd struggling in the plastic bag while being buried implying hes getting buried alive. After burying him the mainstream Weeknd walks forward and keeps doing so until he sees the devil. In which then he shoots it killing it. He has now killed what controls him and gets in the car and drives off looking to see what the future holds him. However he sees that hes still not as happy as he was before The Hills so...

We have Starboy where the mainstream dreaded Weeknd is sitting in his beautiful home until his old self comes up behind him and strangles the mainstream Weeknd with the own plastic bag he buried him alive with. Then we see the old Weeknd who has the short Trilogy flattop again. We see him with a cross symbolizing either The Weeknd has found Christ, or more simply is using the cross as a representation of resurrection. He then goes around his house destroying all the memorabilia that represented the mainstream Weeknd. However after this he goes in a car with a cat which shortly after turns into a panther this could be him saying hes going back to his bigger and better self but I dont really know. So in the end in all this I think this Starboy video shows us hes back to making he likes as well as what we like. 

PLEASE LIKE THIS COMMENT I SPENT SO MUCH TIME DECYPHERING ALL THE VIDEOS CONNECTED!!!

He also says in Tell Your Friends, "We are not the same I am too reckless, I dont wanna go in that direction." And all of this is being said while his old self is being buried, (his old self still has the dreads because at this time he didnt want to cut them off until for Starboy.)

Wow, its obvious in the new album that he's embracing this pop sound. He will eventually see the downsides and go back.

You can get addicted to a certain kind of sadness
Like resignation to the end, always the end
So when we found that we could not make sense
Well you said that we would still be friends
But I'll admit that I was glad it was over

This one I can actually relate to and is probably the main reason why I chose to write this entire explanation. Itâ€™s true you can get addicted to a certain kind of sadness, or you can get sad from it. Nostalgia, remembering the good times, with his fiancÃ©. I get lost in it, especially in these depressing and dark times, but we should remember the past, not get stuck in it. He gets a bit more nostalgic remembering the good times. In the first verse, he says now and then except now he gets a bit sad. I think this is his recovery, and when she integrated into his life, left a hole where she came in, he started missing her more. After they broke up, he thinks he can do fine without her, he then later starts missing her even more.

Wow, one paragraph about 1 line, Iâ€™ll make this quick(er).
The next is like resignation to the end, which mirrors what I said about nostalgia. If you were going to die, you think back to your happiest moments (I hope). Always the end, itâ€™s always the end that has you wishing to go back. You never miss it until you lose it is kind of the message. Next line is simple; he realizes (presumably after a fight) how they couldnâ€™t seek common ground, that they shouldnâ€™t be together. A toxic relationship which is an all to real thing. She said that they could be friends, but after they realized that couldnâ€™t work out, she started avoiding him. If youâ€™ve been dating for a while, then itâ€™s harder to get out of a relationship. Itâ€™s hard to let go because youâ€™re hoping it will work out. Then he says that Iâ€™m glad that we stopped pretending we could even be friends.

Verse 3:

So after he admits their relationship is toxic, and she cuts him off, he says that she canâ€™t completely just ignore him. She canâ€™t just pretend like nothing ever happened, and he found acceptance. She did not accept the relationship they had and basically erase her identity. Start out fresh, which is a good idea in theory but in practice is just so wrong. She treats him like a stranger and ignores everything. He keeps bugging her (not a good idea, you need space so both of you can recover) and she changes her phone number and any records that she was there. He then accepts that as well, realizing he doesnâ€™t need her at all anymore. Finally, all thatâ€™s left of her is his memory of her, and what she represents. A hopeful life, a happy family and something for each other to lean on.

Verse 4:

Now and then I think of all the times you screwed me over
But had me believing it was always something that I'd done
But I don't wanna live that way
Reading into every word you say

This time, it switches POV to her. This was a change to show her reasoning. Now that sheâ€™s out of this toxic relationship, she recalls â€œall the times you screwed me overâ€. He was the real toxicity of this relationship. He was abusive, and manipulated her. He always blamed her for something that he did as â€˜leverageâ€™. She figures out all of her troubles, struggles that she endured with him, weâ€™re all his fault. Thatâ€™s why she stooped so low, she never wanted to meet someone else. Sometimes people donâ€™t even realize theyâ€™re toxic, it just depends on what they do. Donâ€™t blame yourself until you actually see it without rose-tinted glasses. He wants the relationship back, but when they broke up he said he wouldnâ€™t care about her.  She finds independence, freedom and acceptance. She finds him thinking about her and she tells him the time when they broke up. She realizes the relationship was toxic, and he gets adamant. Refuses, and when she finally wins the argument, he storms off yelling that he wonâ€™t care what would happen to her. I guess he realizes it too late, when the relationship was over.

This time, he wants repentance, he wants to show her heâ€™s changed. But, from the context of the song, their relationship must have been going on for a while. Again, taking blame for something she didnâ€™t do. The reason why this verse was repeated (and not just because itâ€™s a song) was to send home the fact that she truly doesnâ€™t care for him. Summary:This took me an hour to write, so Iâ€™m looking for LIKES! Iâ€™m just kidding, like if you want but please donâ€™t feel forced to. He recalls his relationship with her, hoping that she could be the missing piece in his puzzle and vice versa. He starts trying to remember more of her, of what she was like, getting addicted to a â€œcertain kind of sadnessâ€. Â Nostalgia, or the sadness of how we canâ€™t go back to it. I miss you baby. -unregistered number". My heart sank realizing it was his phone. My hands started shaking but after a few minutes I started preparing and then went to work. By lunch time I decided to take the rest of the day off. I went home and saw an unfamiliar car leaving our parking space. I went into our apartment and found him cleaning up everything. He froze in shock seeing me. I came close and kissed his forehead and softly whispered to him, "It's okay. I know I'm not the only one."
That was the 3rd and final time I cared. I'm getting my life back together now. I'll be okay without him. ğŸ™ƒ

I found out my wife cheated on me in July of 2019. The divorce was officially settled in September. We had been married since 2007 and had known each other since 9th grade. I had suspicions that she had been cheating on me,  but she constantly told me I was being insecure or worrying for no reason. I went along with it for a while, but something didnâ€™t feel right. She was coming home late, she didnâ€™t show me the same level of affection, would never let me see her phone, and she was always â€œbusy.â€ Sheâ€™d been cheating on me since 2015, but I let my love and trust for her blind me. She took advantage of me and my kindness. The pain I felt listening to this song and the way I was able to relate to it made me cry more than I ever have in my life, and that crying made me feel better than I ever have. The morale of the story here is: 1) Never let people take advantage of your kindness 2) make sure you choose the right person when you are looking for a relationship, what I mean is make sure both of you are on the same page. This song really means something to me. I listen to a lot of music, as im sure everyone else does too. But nothing is quite like this one. It connects all of my best memories and every time I listen to it, I revisit them. My grandma, my sister, my girlfriend, my best friends, Spider-Man, all the good stuff. Obviously you don't know me, but reading the comments, its awesome to see this song has a similar effect on other people. I remember one time I was in a bit of an argument with my S.O and it was a big one, which does not happen often. I was driving her home, and this song came over my Playlist. By the time I drove in the lane way, and the song had faded out, we were both teared up, and we just hugged for like 20 minutes. I dont even remember what the argument was, but if a song can have that kind of positive effect on people, then whomever created it did so with unbelievable passion, positivity and creativity. Thanks Swae and Posty, yall are life savers

I know little of contemporary dance. I do know that focusing on the dance, the movements themselves are the goal. If you can, forget the difference in age or the fact one was male and one female. Dismiss that they are even human (the dance mimics animal behavior). I saw one "being"  (shia) longing for connection, friendship, love... acceptance. The whole time, trying to win the others trust. The other "being" (maddie) a wounded soul who knows pain, is mistrustful, hesitant and fiercely defensive in her movements for most of the dance. I saw nothing sexual in the dance or movements. There was no lust conveyed to these eyes. At the end he had finally won her trust and she sees him for what he is...a friend, an ally. But the cage (society perhaps) will never allow them to be together and hence...the tragic ending. Fear of being alone drives most of us. I'm sure a large segment of the population can relate to this. It was beautiful.

When a monkey dances better than you

My mom really liked Coldplay, and enjoyed every song of their, but especially she loved this one, and every time I was asking her "What are you listening to?" smiling, knowing that this is her favorite tune, she replied every time "The monkeys!!!" with such cheer enthusiasm, that you could still see her laughing after a month of non-stop listening. I can still remember the synthesizer that was keeping her up all night, waking me up half in half an hour until 3 to 8 A.M. every morning. :D She was... 67 - because she never had the pleasure to celebrate her 68th birthday on 4 May 2019... she died in the silent night on 4th January 2019, and yes, I know this is late to say, but with all this quarantine thing, I found the occasion to share this memory of her and my life with you. May she rest in peace.

The song was written in response to the death of Johnathan Ball, 3, and Tim Parry, 12, who had been killed in the IRA bombing in Warrington, northwestern England, when two devices hidden in litter bins were detonated. Johnathan Ball died at the scene of the bombing as a result of his shrapnel inflicted injuries and, five days later, Tim Parry lost his life as a result of fatal head injuries. Fifty-four others were injured, some seriously. The two boys had gone shopping to buy Mother's Day cards on one of the town's busiest shopping streets.

Realise you are a sinner; Isaiah 64:6 (UKJV) But we are all as an unclean thing, and all our righteousnesses(the quality of being morally right) are as filthy rags; and we all do fade as a leaf; and our iniquities, like the wind, have taken us away.

Deserving hell for sins
Realise that you deserve hell for your sins; 
Romans 6:23 plainly states that the wages of sin is DEATH.Â In Genesis 2:17 God warned Adam and Eve that they would die THE DAY they ate of the forbidden fruit.Â They disobeyed God, but didn't DIE physically until hundreds of years later.Â Why? It's because they DIED SPIRITUALLY that awful day, and all mankind has been born spiritually dead since (Romans 5:12).Â Please understand that spiritual death and the second death areÂ notÂ the same.Â Every person who is not born again is ALREADY spiritually dead.Â The second death is Gehenna, i.e., the Lake of Fire (Revelation 20:11-15).Â All those who die in their sins, without being born again( that is believing that Jesus Christ got crucified and shed his blood for their sins, buried and rose again in the third day and alive now in heaven), will be arraigned, prosecuted, and sentenced atÂ The Great White Throne of JudgmentÂ and then cast into the Lake of Fire forever.Â 

Repent
So repent, Repenting means: to change your mind; a sincere turning away, in heart, mind and action; Therefore God wants you to repent of sinful values and of sinful living. God wants you to decide to follow Him and to make Jesus the Lord of your life.

No other way 
If you want to go to heaven, you've got to go through the door marked "Jesus Christ." There is no other entrance. 
By no other entrance it means belief in gods, Buddha, Muhammad or other beings or objects cannot save you; But only belief in Jesus Christ our Lord can save you.
No works can save you, there is no physical thing you can do to get saved but you are only saved through faith at what Jesus did for you as simple as that. Ephesians 2:8-9 For by grace are ye saved through faith; and that not of yourselves: it is the gift of God:
Not of works, lest any man should boast.

Believe 
All you need to do is to truly believe with your heart and confess with your mouth that Jesus Christ suffered and got crucified and shed his blood for your sins at the cross, He was buried but rose again on the third day just to prove he was God and now alive in heaven. After that you will receive the holy spirit and you will know that you are going to heaven after death or when Jesus comes back while you are still alive.

After believing at Christ as the savior you must change your ways and try to stay away from bad works or sins as hard as possible, you must show that you are a new individual in Christ. e.g stopping fornication, getting drunk, homosexual acts, masturbation, pornography e.t.c. 
As a human you will still fall at some sins of course as no human is perfect, but you must not swim in sin you must try your best to fight against sins and live a righteous life. The point is there is only right and wrong, good and bad, both of which knows no sides. As an Irish man I pray that one day we all understand this message of unity (not as an island but as compassionate human beings for one another),  instead of the narcissistic exploitation of compassionate points wasted on social media. I don't care who officially owns land, we are all one and the same. RIP Dolores o'riordan

The music video is about a Bolivian ğŸ‡§ğŸ‡´ legend that tells the story of a deaf boy who fled from his abusive home and found a stray dog ğŸ• that accompanied him since then. After living on the streets. He discovers that he has the special ability of perceiving troubled people - which he can heal by screaming (screaming that its said to be as loud as an earthquake and a tornadoğŸŒª)

One day, he finds an old man who was being stoned by villagers while being taunted and ridiculed (hence why the old man has a dusty face) the boy intervened and by screaming, he resolved the situation and revived the old manâ€™s heart (in the video, by buying him a new heart).

Old man and kid later meet a disfigured man who was abused, and was considered a leper by society (Called Kusillo in Bolivia). The disfigured man reveals that he is a prophet who was cursed by the devil ğŸ‘¹ (El Tio) because he didnâ€™t worship him anymore and abandoned the town where the demon resided. 

ğŸ‘¹ El Tio is considered the lord of the underworld, to whom mortal people offer gifts in exchange for protection, or to ease his anger. 

The prophet (masked man) said anybody who could hear the demon would fall under his controlğŸŒ€. He told them that the demon could be found across a desert (Uyuni salt flats), where there was a town where people worshipped el tio ğŸ‘¹ - and the story said that el tio cursed the people in that town to kill themselves.

Together they start the journey to find the town, and arrive at a mine where the demon ğŸ‘¹ resided but they knew that everybody with their hearing intact could be cursed by el TioğŸ‘¹ or be directed to kill each other. 

That is why boy had to face the demon  alone and over voice him with his scream to stop him from cursing others.(the ultimate sacrifice - and why the two man and the dog left- to avoid getting under el tio ğŸ‘¹ control ğŸŒ€)

The video has an open ending, considering that El Tio is the lord of the underworld who rules in the mines, and miners usually sacrifice a llama as a tribute from time to time to avoid being cursed.
